<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="182" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,295,934]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">
<bibRefCitation author="Novak, V." box="[151,311,295,321]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" pagination="417 - 453" refId="ref4901" refString="Novak, V. (2020) Subfamily Alleculinae Laporte, 1840. In: Iwan, D. &amp; Lobl, I. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 5. Tenebrionoidea. Leiden, Brill, 417 - 453 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004434998 _ 004" type="book chapter" year="2020">Novák (2020)</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[634,792,295,321]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[806,935,295,321]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[949,994,296,322]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Iran</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1054,1168,295,321]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
. Originally, the species was described from the Tedzhen-Murghab oasis (
<collectingCountry box="[709,867,331,358]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
) and the Alai Ridge (
<collectingCountry box="[1113,1245,331,357]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Seidlitz, G. C. M. von" box="[1268,1424,331,358]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" pagination="1 - 305" refId="ref5072" refString="Seidlitz, G. C. M. von (1896) Alleculidae. In: Naturgeschichte der Insecten Deutschlands. Begonnen von Dr. W. F. Erichson, fortgesetzt von Prof. Dr. H. Schaum, Dr. G. Kraatz, H. v. Kiesenwetter, Julius Weise, Edm. Reitter und Dr. G. Seidlitz. Erste Abtheilung Coleoptera. Funfter Band. Zweite Halfte. Lieferungen 1 - 3. Nicolaische Verlags-Buchhandlung, Berlin, pp. 1 - 305." type="book chapter" year="1896">Seidlitz 1896</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Dubrovina, M. I." box="[151,345,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" pagination="367 - 376" refId="ref3823" refString="Dubrovina, M. I. (1973) New subgenus and new species of pollen beetles of the genus Isomira Muls. (Coleoptera, Alleculidae) from Middle Asia. Entomologicheskoe obozrenie, 52 (2), 367 - 376. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1973">Dubrovina (1973</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dubrovina, M. I." box="[356,413,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" pagination="123 - 136" refId="ref3871" refString="Dubrovina, M. I. (1982) A review of beetles of the genus Isomira Muls. (Coleoptera, Alleculidae) of the USSR. Entomologicheskoe obozrenie. 61 (1), 123 - 136. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1982">1982</bibRefCitation>
) assumed that specimens of the 
<typeStatus box="[772,820,368,394]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">type</typeStatus>
series from the Alai Ridge belong to a different species because such a wide gap in the range is very doubtful. The species is distributed in deserts of Central Asia, in floodplains of Tedzhen, Murghab and Amu Darya rivers. Its presence was confirmed in 
<collectingCountry box="[1176,1331,439,465]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1391,1436,440,466]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[159,462,475,501]" country="Iran" name="Khorasan-e Razavi" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Razavi Khorasan Province</collectingRegion>
: Sarahs) (
<bibRefCitation author="Dubrovina, M. I." box="[570,757,475,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" pagination="367 - 376" refId="ref3823" refString="Dubrovina, M. I. (1973) New subgenus and new species of pollen beetles of the genus Isomira Muls. (Coleoptera, Alleculidae) from Middle Asia. Entomologicheskoe obozrenie, 52 (2), 367 - 376. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1973">Dubrovina 1973</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dubrovina, M. I." box="[767,827,475,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" pagination="123 - 136" refId="ref3871" refString="Dubrovina, M. I. (1982) A review of beetles of the genus Isomira Muls. (Coleoptera, Alleculidae) of the USSR. Entomologicheskoe obozrenie. 61 (1), 123 - 136. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1982">1982</bibRefCitation>
). We haven’t analysed specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1267,1393,475,501]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
nor are aware who listed 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seidlitz" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[385,541,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Asiomira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ophtalmica">
<emphasis box="[385,541,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">A. ophtalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from this country, but a record of this species on the Uzbek part of the floodplain of Amu Darya is likely. Specimens from Zagros mountains (
<collectingCountry box="[805,855,547,573]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Iran</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[864,965,548,574]" country="Iran" name="Lorestan" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Lorestan</collectingRegion>
, Dorud), which were figured and described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Novak, V." box="[187,345,583,610]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" pagination="177 - 191" refId="ref4854" refString="Novak, V. (2016) Review of the genus Asiomira (Dubrovina, 1973) stat. nov. (Coleoptera: Tenebrionidae: Alleculinae: Gonoderini). Studies and Reports, Taxonomical Series, 12 (1), 177 - 191." type="journal article" year="2016">Novák (2016)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seidlitz" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[384,542,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Asiomira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ophtalmica">
<emphasis box="[384,542,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">A. ophtalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to represent an undescribed species which is well distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seidlitz" baseAuthorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Asiomira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ophtalmica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">A. ophtalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the structure of the aedeagus (comparing figure 3 here, figure 
<quantity box="[1031,1090,619,645]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.842" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" unit="in" value="23.0">23 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Dubrovina, M. I." box="[1098,1301,619,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" pagination="367 - 376" refId="ref3823" refString="Dubrovina, M. I. (1973) New subgenus and new species of pollen beetles of the genus Isomira Muls. (Coleoptera, Alleculidae) from Middle Asia. Entomologicheskoe obozrenie, 52 (2), 367 - 376. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1973">Dubrovina (1973)</bibRefCitation>
and figures 11, 12 in 
<bibRefCitation author="Novak, V." box="[266,435,655,682]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" pagination="177 - 191" refId="ref4854" refString="Novak, V. (2016) Review of the genus Asiomira (Dubrovina, 1973) stat. nov. (Coleoptera: Tenebrionidae: Alleculinae: Gonoderini). Studies and Reports, Taxonomical Series, 12 (1), 177 - 191." type="journal article" year="2016">Novák (2016))</bibRefCitation>
and elytra (strial punctures are weakly expressed and interstriae slightly convex in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seidlitz" baseAuthorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Asiomira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ophtalmica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">A. ophtalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
unlike specimens from Dorud, 
<collectingCountry box="[633,683,692,718]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Iran</collectingCountry>
). In addition, Novák’s hypothesis on the uniformity of the Irannian specimens and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seidlitz" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[325,483,727,754]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Asiomira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ophtalmica">
<emphasis box="[325,342,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[357,483,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">ophtalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
implicates a doubtful distributional gap in the range of 
<emphasis box="[1121,1287,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seidlitz" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[1121,1283,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Asiomira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ophtalmica">A. ophtalmica</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
We leave Dr Vladimír Novák the opportunity to describe a new species from Dorud.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,295,934]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">
To sum it up, the distribution range of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seidlitz" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[658,818,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Asiomira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ophtalmica">
<emphasis box="[658,818,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">A. ophtalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes 
<collectingCountry box="[932,1090,799,825]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1104,1149,800,826]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Iran</collectingCountry>
(only the eastern border areas with 
<collectingCountry box="[275,434,835,862]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[455,584,836,862]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
(until the 
<typeStatus box="[704,807,835,861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">lectotype</typeStatus>
will be designated, preferably from 
<collectingCountry box="[1223,1380,835,862]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,277,871,897]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
under question. We haven`t included Alai Ridge in the distribution of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seidlitz" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[1080,1239,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Asiomira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ophtalmica">
<emphasis box="[1080,1239,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">A. ophtalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1255,1322,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,761,785]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,744]" captionTargetId="figure-20@2.[151,1436,166,744]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Distribution of the extant species of Asiomira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5785419" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5785419/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="182">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), because this mountain system is large, while the exact collecting locality is unknown.
</paragraph>
